SIMPLE: nudity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nudity
<hw>Nu"di*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Nudities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>nudit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being nude; nakedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is nude or naked; naked part; undrapped or
unclothed portion;</def> <specif>esp.</specif> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld>,
<def>the human figure represented unclothed; any representation of
nakedness; -- chiefly used in the plural and in a bad sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There are no such licenses permitted in poetry any more than in
painting, to design and color obscene <qex>nudities</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nudnik</ent>⟦br⟧
